criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age 18-64 years; a new or recurrent episode of neck pain present for more than 4
             weeks, but no longer than 12 weeks;

          -  neck pain that could extend to the shoulder region or upper extremities, and be
             accompanied by headache, but neck pain was more painful;

          -  the patient agreed not to take medication or receive other treatment for neck pain
             during the course of the study (paracetamol 500 mg 4 times a day was allowed as rescue
             medication);

          -  and a baseline pain level of at least 4 on the 11-point numerical rating scale.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Exclusion criteria were treatment with any of the interventions during 6 months prior
             to recruitment to the study; specific neck pain due to fracture, neoplasm, infection,
             inflammatory arthropathy, radiculopathy or myelopathy;

          -  factors contraindicating manipulation, such as blood coagulation disorders, long-term
             use of corticosteroids, anticoagulant medications, history of neck surgery, stroke or
             transient ischaemic attacks; plans to relocate;

          -  inability to read or understand English;

          -  and third-party liability or workers' compensation claims.
